---
description: Pre-commit gate. Affected-only review of the staged set, writes the marker the PreToolUse hook reads. Usually invoked automatically by the hook, but can be run manually to pre-warm.
---

The pre-commit gate now runs **in-process** via `framework gate`.

**How it works:**

The `PreToolUse` hook in `.claude/settings.json` fires automatically on every `git commit`. It calls `uv run framework gate`, which reviews the affected staged set, writes `.framework/audit/marker.json`, and exits 0 (PASS / skip-neutral) or 1 (FAIL). The hook blocks the commit (exit 2) on a non-zero gate exit.

**Skip-neutral by default:** if no AI review backend is configured (fresh project), `framework gate` degrades gracefully and writes a PASS marker — commits are never blocked solely for lack of a backend.

**Opt in to AI review:**
```bash
uv run framework review-config set-backend api       # paid Anthropic API (requires ANTHROPIC_RUNTIME_API_KEY)
uv run framework review-config set-backend subagent  # free CC subscription
```

**Manual pre-warm** (run before the commit to surface findings early):
```bash
uv run framework gate
```

**Inspect findings:**
```bash
cat .framework/audit/latest/audit-report.md
```

There are no prepare/Workflow/finalize steps — the gate is a single command.
